MIT License

automatised-pipeline — a Rust MCP server that indexes any Rust / Python /
TypeScript codebase into a LadybugDB property graph, resolves imports and
call chains across files, detects functional communities via Leiden-class
algorithms, traces execution flows from entry points, builds a hybrid
BM25 + sparse TF-IDF + RRF search index, and exposes all of it to AI
agents through twenty-three MCP tools. Read-only intelligence: the server
never writes code, opens PRs, or runs CI; it tells the system what is
true about the code so the next stage can reason without guessing. Part
of the ai-architect ecosystem (https://github.com/cdeust/Cortex,
 https://github.com/cdeust/zetetic-team-subagents,
 https://github.com/cdeust/prd-spec-generator).

