The graph-theoretic and information-retrieval algorithms used in this
software (Louvain community detection with C2 repair, BM25, RRF rank
fusion, tree-sitter AST parsing, Tarjan strongly-connected-components)
are sourced from published research; citations are documented inline in
the source via `// source:` annotations and in the project's `docs/`
directory. The MIT license covers this implementation; it does not
assert ownership over the underlying algorithms, which remain
attributable to their original authors.
